She's not answering
my texts. Stiles.

64
00:04:15.839 --> 00:04:18.239
It could just be a
coincidence. all right?

65
00:04:18.308 --> 00:04:20.042
A seriously amazing coincidence.

66
00:04:20.110 --> 00:04:21.910
Just help me find her. okay?

67
00:04:23.330 --> 00:04:25.210
Do you see her? No.

68
00:04:57.063 --> 00:04:58.343
You scared the hell outta me.

69
00:04:59.382 --> 00:05:00.582
You're okay.

70
00:05:00.650 --> 00:05:02.884
Once my heart starts
beating again. yeah.

71
00:05:06.222 --> 00:05:08.072
What?

72
00:05:08.141 --> 00:05:09.635
I'm just happy to see you.

73
00:05:09.659 --> 00:05:11.988
<i>Attention. students.
this is your principal.</i>

74
00:05:12.012 --> 00:05:14.657
<i>I know you're all wondering about
the incident that occurred last night</i>

75
00:05:14.681 --> 00:05:16.080
<i>to one of our buses.</i>

76
00:05:16.149 --> 00:05:18.594
<i>While the police work to
determine what happened.</i>

77
00:05:18.618 --> 00:05:21.152
<i>classes will proceed
as scheduled.</i>

78
00:05:21.221 --> 00:05:23.141
<i>Thank you.</i>

79
00:05:23.774 --> 00:05:25.540
Save me a seat at lunch?

80
00:05:25.608 --> 00:05:26.741
Yeah.

81
00:05:38.621 --> 00:05:40.781
What are you
looking at. asswipe?

82
00:05:48.832 --> 00:05:50.342
Maybe it was my
blood on the door.

83
00:05:50.366 --> 00:05:52.100
Could have been animal blood.

84
00:05:52.169 --> 00:05:53.879
You know. maybe you
caught a rabbit or something.

85
00:05:53.903 --> 00:05:55.336
And did what?

86
00:05:55.405 --> 00:05:56.938
Ate it. Raw?

87
00:05:57.007 --> 00:05:59.474
No. you stopped to bake
it in a little werewolf oven.

88
00:05:59.542 --> 00:06:01.437
I don't know. you're the one
who can't remember anything.

89
00:06:01.461 --> 00:06:04.240
Mr. Stilinski. if that's your
idea of a hushed whisper.

90
00:06:04.264 --> 00:06:07.677
you might want to pull the
headphones out every once in a while.

91
00:06:07.701 --> 00:06:10.729
I think you and Mr. McCall would
benefit from a little distance. yes?

92
00:06:10.753 --> 00:06:12.754
No.

93
00:06:14.641 --> 00:06:17.454
Let me know if the separation
anxiety gets to be too much.

94
00:06:28.689 --> 00:06:31.489
Hey. I think they
found something.

95
00:06:38.215 --> 00:06:39.847
That's not a rabbit.

96
00:06:42.669 --> 00:06:44.736
Okay.

97
00:06:44.805 --> 00:06:46.482
This is good. this is good.

98
00:06:46.506 --> 00:06:48.284
He got up. he's not dead.

99
00:06:48.308 --> 00:06:50.308
Dead guys can't do that.

100
00:06:51.612 --> 00:06:53.078
Stiles...

101
00:06:54.881 --> 00:06:56.398
I did that.

102
00:07:02.689 --> 00:07:04.489
But dreams aren't memories.

103
00:07:04.558 --> 00:07:06.858
Then it wasn't a dream.

104
00:07:06.927 --> 00:07:11.396
Something happened last
night. and I can't remember what.

105
00:07:11.465 --> 00:07:13.576
What makes you so sure that
Derek even has all the answers?

106
00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:17.185
Because during the full
moon he wasn't changed.

107
00:07:17.254 --> 00:07:18.537
He was in total control

108
00:07:18.605 --> 00:07:20.182
while I was running around
in the middle of the night

109
00:07:20.206 --> 00:07:21.651
attacking some
totally innocent guy.

110
00:07:21.675 --> 00:07:23.715
You don't know that.
I don't not know it.

111
00:07:25.028 --> 00:07:26.772
I can't go out with
Allison. I have to cancel.

112
00:07:26.796 --> 00:07:28.741
No. you're not canceling. okay?

113
00:07:28.765 --> 00:07:31.925
You can't just cancel your
entire life. We'll figure it out.

114
00:07:33.019 --> 00:07:34.585
Figure what out?

115
00:07:34.654 --> 00:07:35.654
Ha!

116
00:07:36.873 --> 00:07:37.939
Just. uh. homework.

117
00:07:38.007 --> 00:07:39.941
Yeah.

118
00:07:40.009 --> 00:07:42.249
Why is she sitting with us?

119
