the whole group date thing.

159
00:09:42.849 --> 00:09:44.526
And then out of nowhere
comes that phrase.

160
00:09:44.550 --> 00:09:46.017
Hang out.

161
00:09:46.086 --> 00:09:48.330
You don't hang out with
hot girls. okay? It's like death.

162
00:09:48.354 --> 00:09:51.256
Once it's hanging out. you might
as well be her gay best friend.

163
00:09:51.324 --> 00:09:52.804
You and Danny can
start hanging out.

164
00:09:52.859 --> 00:09:55.772
How is this happening? I
either killed a guy or I didn't.

165
00:09:55.796 --> 00:09:57.396
I don't think Danny
likes me very much.

166
00:09:57.463 --> 00:09:59.809
I ask Allison on a date.
and now we're hanging out.

167
00:09:59.833 --> 00:10:01.532
Am I not attractive to gay guys?

168
00:10:01.601 --> 00:10:04.747
I make first line. and the team
captain wants to destroy me. and now...

169
00:10:04.771 --> 00:10:06.232
Now I'm gonna be late for work.

170
00:10:06.256 --> 00:10:08.156
Wait. Scott. you didn't...

171
00:10:08.224 --> 00:10:10.691
Am I attractive to gay guy...

172
00:10:10.760 --> 00:10:12.993
You didn't answer my question.

173
00:10:21.988 --> 00:10:24.723
Sorry. Sorry.

174
00:10:24.791 --> 00:10:26.869
You're all of two minutes late.

175
00:10:26.893 --> 00:10:29.527
I just don't want you
to think I'm slacking.

176
00:10:29.596 --> 00:10:34.265
Scott. I guarantee you. you're one
of the least slacking kids in this town.

177
00:10:48.882 --> 00:10:52.751
Hey. I see somebody's
ready to get their stitches out.

178
00:10:52.819 --> 00:10:54.685
Hey there. Scott. You
staying out of trouble?

179
00:10:57.557 --> 00:10:58.572
Yeah.

180
00:11:00.543 --> 00:11:01.987
Hey. listen. while I'm here.

181
00:11:02.011 --> 00:11:04.040
you mind taking a look at those
pictures I was telling you about?

182
00:11:04.064 --> 00:11:06.325
Sacramento still can't
determine an animal.

183
00:11:06.349 --> 00:11:08.182
I'm not exactly an expert.

184
00:11:10.036 --> 00:11:12.556
This is the guy who
was attacked in the bus?

185
00:11:12.589 --> 00:11:13.905
Yeah.

186
00:11:13.973 --> 00:11:16.213
And we found wolf hairs
on Laura Hale's body.

187
00:11:16.626 --> 00:11:17.659
A wolf?

188
00:11:20.580 --> 00:11:23.081
I mean. I think I read somewhere

189
00:11:23.149 --> 00:11:25.561
that wolves haven't been in
California for. like. 60 years.

190
00:11:25.585 --> 00:11:28.603
True enough. but wolves
are highly migratory.

191
00:11:28.671 --> 00:11:30.282
They could have wandered
in from another state

192
00:11:30.306 --> 00:11:33.174
driven by impulse or
strong enough memory.

193
00:11:33.944 --> 00:11:35.543
Wolves have memories?

194
00:11:35.611 --> 00:11:38.162
Longer-term memories. yes.

195
00:11:38.231 --> 00:11:40.614
If associated
with a primal drive.

196
00:11:40.683 --> 00:11:42.144
- See this one here?
- Yeah.

197
00:11:42.168 --> 00:11:43.701
Those are claw marks.

198
00:11:43.770 --> 00:11:45.753
A wolf would have
gone for the throat

199
00:11:45.822 --> 00:11:47.888
or the spinal
cord with its teeth.

200
00:11:47.957 --> 00:11:50.608
So what do you think.
it's a mountain lion?

201
00:11:50.676 --> 00:11:52.710
I don't know.

202
00:11:52.779 --> 00:11:54.629
A wolf could chase
down its prey.

203
00:11:54.698 --> 00:11:56.531
hobbling it by
tearing at the ankles.

204
00:12:01.604 --> 00:12:03.104
And then the throat.

205
00:12:10.630 --> 00:12:15.232
Is my beautiful. talented. and wonderful
son actually bringing me dinner?

206
00:12:15.301 --> 00:12:18.347
Thought you wouldn't mind
skipping the cafeteria tonight.

207
00:12:18.371 --> 00:12:20.688
You are the most
thoughtful. loving.

208
00:12:20.757 --> 00:12:23.458
most conniving
little con artist ever.

209
00:12:23.527 --> 00:12:25.576
You are so not getting
the car tomorrow night.

210
00:12:26.179 --> 00:12:27.645
Mom. What?

211
00:12:27.713 --> 00:12:29.713
There's a curfew. no car.

212
00:12:30.600 --> 00:12:32.416
But I will take this.

213
00:12:33.152 --> 00:12:34.619
Love you.

214
00:12:34.687 --> 00:12:36.154
Love you. too.

215
00:13:18.398 --> 00:13:20.064
Mr. Meyers.

216
00:13:27.790 --> 00:13:29.456
Are you okay?

217
00:13:40.637 --> 00:13:43.071
What the hell are
you doing in here?

218
00:13:43.139 --> 00:13:44.839
Get out! Now. go!

219
00:13:44.908 --> 00:13:46.107
Go. go!

220
00:14:18.391 --> 00:14:20.231
It looks pretty
deserted. dispatch.

221
00:14:20.293 --> 00:14:22.271
Did you want me
to take a look inside?

222
00:14:22.295 --> 00:14:24.077
<i>Unit 16. it's county property.</i>

223
00:14:24.146 --> 00:14:26.331
<i>Order's to make
sure it's vacant.</i>

224
00:14:26.399 --> 00:14:29.799
I don't... I don't
think anyone's home.

225
00:14:30.069 --> 00:14:33.371
<i>For the love of God. 16. go
inside and see if anyone's in there.</i>

226
00:14:33.439 --> 00:14:34.772
Copy that.

227
00:14:40.630 --> 00:14:42.247
Don't do that.

228
00:15:14.364 --> 00:15:15.879
Okay. I'm coming.

229
00:15:16.615 --> 00:15:17.965
I'm coming.

230
00:15:39.372 --> 00:15:40.921
I know you can hear me.

231
00:15:43.659 --> 00:15:44.759
I need your help.

232
00:15:56.172 --> 00:15:58.171
Okay.

233
00:15:58.240 --> 00:16:00.051
I know I was part of
you getting arrested

234
00:16:00.075 --> 00:16:02.787
and that we basically announced
you being here to the hunters.

235
00:16:02.811 --> 00:16:06.163
I also don't know what
happened to your sister.

236
00:16:06.232 --> 00:16:09.300
But I think I did
something last night.

237
00:16:09.369 --> 00:16:12.236
I had a dream about someone.

238
00:16:12.305 --> 00:16:14.345
But someone else got hurt.

239
00:16:14.374 --> 00:16:17.153
And it turns out that part of the
dream might have actually happened.

240
00:16:17.177 --> 00:16:18.992
You think you
attacked the driver?

241
00:16:19.061 --> 00:16:21.506
Did you see what
I did last night? No.

242
00:16:21.530 --> 00:16:24.331
Can you at least
tell me the truth?

243
00:16:24.400 --> 00:16:26.645
Am I gonna hurt someone? Yes.

244
00:16:26.669 --> 00:16:28.264
Could I kill someone? Yes.

245
00:16:28.288 --> 00:16:30.848
Am I gonna kill
someone? Probably.

246
00:16:37.113 --> 00:16:41.749
Look. I can show
you how to remember.

247
00:16:41.818 --> 00:16:44.786
I can show you how to control
the shift. even on a full moon.

248
00:16:46.156 --> 00:16:47.676
But it's not gonna
come for free.

249
00:16:48.257 --> 00:16:49.991
What do you want?

250
00:16:50.059 --> 00:16:52.326
You'll find out.

251
00:16:52.395 --> 00:16:54.295
But for now. I'm gonna
give you what you want.

252
00:16:54.363 --> 00:16:56.197
Go back to the bus.

253
00:16:56.265 --> 00:17:00.117
Go inside. See it. feel it.

254
00:17:00.186 --> 00:17:03.938
Let your senses. your sight. smell.
touch. Let them remember for you.

255
00:17:05.174 --> 00:17:06.507
That's it?

256
00:17:06.575 --> 00:17:07.825
Just go back?

257
00:17:07.894 --> 00:17:09.454
Do you want to
know what happened?

258
00:17:10.363 --> 00:17:11.990
I just want to
know if I hurt him.

259
00:17:12.014 --> 00:17:13.581
No. you don't.

260
00:17:14.550 --> 00:17:16.517
You want to know
if you'll hurt her.

261
00:17:31.651 --> 00:17:34.196
Hey. no. just me. Someone
needs to keep watch.

262
00:17:34.220 --> 00:17:35.953
How come I'm always
the guy keeping watch?

263
00:17:36.022 --> 00:17:38.502
Because there's only two of us.

264
00:17:38.558 --> 00:17:41.793
Okay. why's it starting to feel
like you're Batman and I'm Robin?

265
00:17:41.861 --> 00:17:44.144
I don't want to be
Robin all the time.

266
00:17:44.213 --> 00:17:46.764
Nobody's Batman and
Robin any of the time.

267
00:17:46.832 --> 00:17:48.366
Not even some of the time?

268
00:17:48.434 --> 00:17:49.674
Just stay here.

269
00:17:49.735 --> 00:17:51.519
Oh. my God! Fine.

270
00:19:26.115 --> 00:19:27.231
Aah!

271
00:20:14.080 --> 00:20:16.047
Come on. come on. come on.

272
00:20:17.283 --> 00:20:18.799
Go! Go! Go! Go!

273
00:20:25.675 --> 00:20:27.719
Did it work? Did you remember?

274
00:20:27.743 --> 00:20:29.293
Yeah. I was there last night.

275
00:20:29.345 --> 00:20:31.295
And the blood. a
lot of it was mine.

276
00:20:31.364 --> 00:20:32.825
So you did attack him? No.

277
00:20:32.849 --> 00:20:35.699
I saw glowing eyes in the
bus. but they weren't mine.

278
00:20:35.768 --> 00:20:37.617
It was Derek. What
about the driver?

279
00:20:37.686 --> 00:20:39.514
I think I was actually
trying to protect him.

280
00:20:39.538 --> 00:20:42.350
Wait. why would Derek help you
remember that he attacked the driver?

281
00:20:42.374 --> 00:20:43.557
That's what I don't get.

282
00:20:43.626 --> 00:20:45.403
It's got to be a pack thing.

283
00:20:45.427 --> 00:20:48.223
What do you mean? Like an
initiation. You do the kill together.

284
00:20:48.247 --> 00:20:50.659
Because ripping someone's throat
out is a real bonding experience?

285
00:20:50.683 --> 00:20:53.144
Yeah. but you didn't do it.
which means you're not a killer.

286
00:20:53.168 --> 00:20:56.648
And it also means that...
I can go out with Allison.

287
00:20:56.939 --> 00:20:59.250
I was gonna say it
means you won't kill me.

288
00:20:59.274 --> 00:21:00.440
Oh. yeah.

289
00:21:01.043 --> 00:21:02.225
That too.

290
00:21:18.627 --> 00:21:21.061
Mmm. pass.

291
00:21:24.900 --> 00:21:26.166
Pass.

292
00:21:26.719 --> 00:21:28.985
Let me see.

293
00:21:29.054 --> 00:21:35.225
Pass. Pass. Pass on all of it.

294
00:21:35.294 --> 00:21:39.830
God. Allison. respect for your
taste is dwindling by the second.

295
00:21:42.835 --> 00:21:43.955
Hmm.

296
00:21:45.605 --> 00:21:47.771
This.

297
00:21:54.997 --> 00:21:56.263
Dad. hello.

298
00:21:57.583 --> 00:22:00.351
Right. I'm sorry. I
completely forgot to knock.

299
00:22:01.988 --> 00:22:04.371
Hi. Mr. Argent.

300
00:22:04.440 --> 00:22:06.334
Dad. do you need something?

301
00:22:06.358 --> 00:22:07.919
I wanted to tell you that
you'll be staying in tonight.

302
00:22:07.943 --> 00:22:09.821
What? I'm going out
with my friends tonight.

303
00:22:09.845 --> 00:22:12.240
Not when some animal
out there is attacking people.

304
00:22:12.264 --> 00:22:13.797
Dad. Dad...

305
00:22:13.866 --> 00:22:15.243
It's out of my hands.
There's a curfew.

306
00:22:15.267 --> 00:22:17.587
No one's allowed
out past 9:30 p.m.

307
00:22:18.287 --> 00:22:19.870
Hey.

308
00:22:19.939 --> 00:22:21.438
no more arguing.

309
00:22:27.880 --> 00:22:30.114
Someone's daddy's little girl.

310
00:22:31.717 --> 00:22:34.835
Sometimes. But not tonight.

311
00:22:53.456 --> 00:22:54.487
What are you doing?

312
00:22:58.010 --> 00:23:00.895
Eight years gymnastics.
Are you coming?

313
00:23:02.165 --> 00:23:03.664
I'll take the stairs.

314
00:23:11.974 --> 00:23:14.975
You really look like you
know what you're doing.

315
00:23:15.044 --> 00:23:18.812
Used to bowl with my dad. When
was the last time you bowled?

316
00:23:19.681 --> 00:23:22.282
Uh. at a birthday party...

317
00:23:25.054 --> 00:23:27.454
When I was eight.

318
00:23:30.876 --> 00:23:33.577
<i>♪ You never get nervous anymore</i>

319
00:23:33.646 --> 00:23:35.546
<i>♪ So wait up</i>

320
00:23:35.614 --> 00:23:38.499
<i>♪ You never get nervous anymore</i>

321
00:23:38.568 --> 00:23:41.502
<i>♪ What did you want me to say?</i>

322
00:23:41.571 --> 00:23:43.270
<i>♪ Hey!</i>

323
00:23:43.339 --> 00:23:46.223
<i>♪ What did you want me to do?</i>

324
00:23:46.292 --> 00:23:47.758
I'm so bad at this.

325
00:23:55.684 --> 00:23:57.400
<i>♪ Inside the lines</i>

326
00:23:57.469 --> 00:23:59.652
<i>♪ Gotta catch 'em in a paper cup</i>

327
00:23:59.721 --> 00:24:02.572
<i>♪ You never know
when to change your luck</i>

328
00:24:02.641 --> 00:24:05.075
Somebody brought their A game.

329
00:24:05.143 --> 00:24:07.544
Good job.

330
00:24:07.613 --> 00:24:11.098
<i>♪ So introduce
me to your friends</i>

331
00:24:11.167 --> 00:24:14.185
<i>♪ With the music and
the lights and everything ♪</i>

332
00:24:16.055 --> 00:24:18.672
Whoo! Yes!

333
00:24:24.363 --> 00:24:25.603
You're up. McCall.

334
00:24:27.884 --> 00:24:30.684
You can do it. Scott.

335
00:24:54.326 --> 00:24:55.742
Jackson?

336
00:24:57.062 --> 00:24:58.662
Mind shutting up?

337
00:24:58.731 --> 00:25:01.131
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

338
00:25:01.200 --> 00:25:03.728
I'm just flashing back to the
words "I'm a great bowler."

339
00:25:03.752 --> 00:25:06.586
Maybe he just needs
a little warm-up.

340
00:25:06.655 --> 00:25:08.833
Yeah. maybe he just
needs the kiddy bumpers.

341
00:25:10.826 --> 00:25:12.993
Just... Just aim for the middle.

342
00:25:13.062 --> 00:25:15.440
How about you aim for
anything except for the gutter?

343
00:25:15.464 --> 00:25:16.513
Let him concentrate.

344
00:25:21.403 --> 00:25:24.304
Come on. just one pin. please.

345
00:25:35.117 --> 00:25:36.228
Oh!

346
00:25:40.406 --> 00:25:42.106
Oh. great job. McCall.

347
00:25:42.758 --> 00:25:44.975
Man. you are a pro.

348
00:25:45.894 --> 00:25:47.277
Don't worry.

349
00:25:47.345 --> 00:25:49.345
We only just started.

350
00:26:32.775 --> 00:26:34.375
Scott.

351
00:26:34.443 --> 00:26:36.310
You're thinking too much.

352
00:26:36.379 --> 00:26:37.922
I know. I'm sorry.
I'm ruining this.

353
00:26:37.946 --> 00:26:42.149
No. no. not at all. but I
wouldn't mind shutting them up.

354
00:26:42.218 --> 00:26:47.354
so just clear your head and
think about something else.

355
00:26:47.423 --> 00:26:48.688
Like what?

356
00:26:48.757 --> 00:26:50.057
Anything.

357
00:26:51.093 --> 00:26:52.659
Think about me.

358
00:26:54.162 --> 00:26:55.796
Naked.

359
00:27:25.961 --> 00:27:27.811
What did you say to him?

360
00:27:27.880 --> 00:27:30.997
I just gave him
something to think about.

361
00:27:47.165 --> 00:27:48.365
Nice ride.

362
00:27:49.635 --> 00:27:54.838
Black cars. though.
Very hard to keep clean.

363
00:27:54.907 --> 00:27:59.743
I would definitely suggest
a little more maintenance.

364
00:28:01.163 --> 00:28:03.280
If you have something this nice.

365
00:28:03.349 --> 00:28:05.415
you want to take
care of it. right?

366
00:28:08.153 --> 00:28:13.873
Personally. I'm very
protective of the things I love.

367
00:28:13.943 --> 00:28:17.010
But that's something I
learned from my family.

368
00:28:18.246 --> 00:28:21.214
And you don't have
much of that these days.

369
00:28:23.586 --> 00:28:24.617
Do you?

370
00:28:38.950 --> 00:28:41.685
There we go.

371
00:28:41.754 --> 00:28:44.704
You can actually look
through your windshield now.

372
00:28:44.773 --> 00:28:47.874
See how that makes
everything so much clearer?

373
00:28:52.047 --> 00:28:54.487
You forgot to check the oil.

374
00:29:01.056 --> 00:29:02.189
Check the man's oil.

375
00:29:09.782 --> 00:29:10.981
Looks good to me.

376
00:29:11.766 --> 00:29:13.233
Drive safely.

377
00:29:34.272 --> 00:29:37.057
That is seriously amazing.

378
00:29:37.125 --> 00:29:40.694
Jackson. how
many strikes is that?

379
00:29:40.763 --> 00:29:42.062
It's six.

380
00:29:43.749 --> 00:29:45.749
In a row.

381
00:29:45.817 --> 00:29:47.768
Something just clicked. I guess.

382
00:29:47.836 --> 00:29:49.553
Maybe it's natural talent.

383
00:29:49.621 --> 00:29:51.938
I could use some natural talent.

384
00:29:52.007 --> 00:29:54.407
You mind helping me
out this time. Scott?

385
00:29:55.377 --> 00:29:57.617
No. you're good. Go for it.

386
00:29:59.231 --> 00:30:01.665
Thanks for the
vote of confidence.

387
00:30:03.685 --> 00:30:05.218
Hey. I'll help.

388
00:30:05.287 --> 00:30:07.653
How about I just
try this on my own?

389
00:30:25.156 --> 00:30:28.308
I think I'm getting
the hang of it.

390
00:30:28.377 --> 00:30:30.043
That was sort of perfect form.

391
00:30:30.962 --> 00:30:32.042
Was it?

392
00:30:33.949 --> 00:30:37.467
Maybe you should stop
pretending to suck just for his benefit.

393
00:30:37.536 --> 00:30:41.038
Trust me. I do plenty of
sucking just for his benefit.

394
00:30:50.448 --> 00:30:51.528
Nice shot. man.

395
00:30:57.606 --> 00:31:00.251
Listen. I know we both
didn't want to be here.

396
00:31:00.275 --> 00:31:03.635
But the thing is we don't
have to hate each other.

397
00:31:04.162 --> 00:31:05.846
I don't hate you.

398
00:31:05.914 --> 00:31:07.681
I just don't believe you.

399
00:31:07.749 --> 00:31:10.295
You know. you got everyone thinking
everything's fine and normal about you.

400
00:31:10.319 --> 00:31:12.686
but I know something's off.

401
00:31:13.689 --> 00:31:14.938
You cheated tonight.

402
00:31:16.091 --> 00:31:17.868
How do you cheat in bowling?

403
00:31:17.892 --> 00:31:20.978
I don't know. but you did.

404
00:31:21.046 --> 00:31:24.564
And I don't know if it's
steroids or something weirder.

405
00:31:24.633 --> 00:31:26.299
I'm guessing something weirder

406
00:31:26.368 --> 00:31:28.451
since it's pretty obvious
that you're a freak.

407
00:31:28.520 --> 00:31:30.671
So don't think for a second

408
00:31:30.739 --> 00:31:33.020
I've given up on finding
out what your little secret is.

409
00:31:34.760 --> 00:31:36.404
I don't have any secrets.

410
00:31:36.428 --> 00:31:41.464
Yeah. you do. And
here's the other thing.

411
00:31:41.533 --> 00:31:45.018
I don't know why. but I think
whatever it is you're hiding.

412
00:31:46.388 --> 00:31:48.455
you don't want her to
find out about it. either.

413
00:31:58.617 --> 00:32:01.084
Open your eyes.

414
00:32:05.090 --> 00:32:07.457
Open your eyes.

415
00:32:10.395 --> 00:32:12.228
Look at me.

416
00:32:19.237 --> 00:32:21.120
What do you remember?

417
00:32:22.874 --> 00:32:24.007
Hale.

418
00:32:26.428 --> 00:32:27.668
How do you know my name?

419
00:32:29.615 --> 00:32:31.281
I'm sorry.

420
00:32:31.350 --> 00:32:33.033
How do you know me?

421
00:32:33.868 --> 00:32:35.902
I'm sorry.

422
00:32:46.949 --> 00:32:48.999
<i>Dr. Damon. telephone. please.</i>

423
00:32:49.067 --> 00:32:50.800
Girl. I am out of here.

424
00:32:50.869 --> 00:32:53.769
There's a DVR at home
full of unwatched TV.

425
00:32:53.838 --> 00:32:57.407
waiting to remind me how
ridiculously single I really am.

426
00:33:01.980 --> 00:33:04.614
Rose. call a code. Room 137.

427
00:33:24.536 --> 00:33:29.406
So do you think we could
hang out again soon?

428
00:33:31.009 --> 00:33:32.025
Definitely.

429
00:33:32.094 --> 00:33:34.744
But I have to admit something.

430
00:33:37.082 --> 00:33:38.781
I'm not big on group dates.

431
00:33:38.850 --> 00:33:40.050
So next time.

432
00:33:40.752 --> 00:33:42.268
just the two of us.

433
00:33:42.337 --> 00:33:44.618
I could totally
handle more of that.

434
00:33:45.174 --> 00:33:46.639
Great.

435
00:33:49.261 --> 00:33:50.927
Allison?

436
00:33:50.996 --> 00:33:54.664
<i>♪ Lord knows.
you're seeing it all</i>

437
00:33:54.733 --> 00:33:57.918
<i>♪ It all</i>

438
00:34:00.689 --> 00:34:04.056
<i>♪ If your heart's on fire</i>

439
00:34:04.125 --> 00:34:08.094
<i>♪ Showing you what one may see</i>

440
00:34:08.163 --> 00:34:11.832
<i>♪ Just give him
your Sunday smile ♪</i>

441
00:34:11.900 --> 00:34:14.534
And I could handle more of that.

442
00:34:33.472 --> 00:34:36.372
Hey. Scott. I'm gonna go to...

443
00:34:37.643 --> 00:34:39.242
Sleep.

444
00:34:41.947 --> 00:34:43.057
Seriously.

445
00:34:54.175 --> 00:34:55.303
Oh. no. no!

446
00:34:57.496 --> 00:34:59.712
Stiles. what the hell
are you doing here?

447
00:34:59.781 --> 00:35:03.221
What am I doing? God. do
either of you even play baseball?

448
00:35:03.252 --> 00:35:05.518
What?

449
00:35:05.587 --> 00:35:08.149
Can you please tell your
friend to use the front door?

450
00:35:08.173 --> 00:35:10.300
But we lock the front door.
He wouldn't be able to get in.

451
00:35:10.324 --> 00:35:11.991
Yeah. exactly.

452
00:35:12.060 --> 00:35:13.938
And. by the way.
do either of you care

453
00:35:13.962 --> 00:35:15.840
that there's a
police-enforced curfew?

454
00:35:15.864 --> 00:35:17.864
No. No. All right then.

455
00:35:17.933 --> 00:35:19.298
Well. you know what?

456
00:35:19.367 --> 00:35:20.895
That's about enough
parenting for me for one night.

457
00:35:20.919 --> 00:35:24.020
so good night. Good night.

458
00:35:27.926 --> 00:35:30.376
What?

459
00:35:30.445 --> 00:35:33.805
My dad left for the hospital 15
minutes ago. It's the bus driver.

460
00:35:35.950 --> 00:35:38.662
They said he
succumbed to his wounds.

461
00:35:38.686 --> 00:35:40.169
Succumbed?

462
00:35:40.238 --> 00:35:42.706
Scott. he's dead.

463
00:35:53.668 --> 00:35:55.702
Derek! I know you're here!

464
00:35:57.289 --> 00:35:58.529
I know what you did!

465
00:36:00.842 --> 00:36:03.009
I didn't do anything.

466
00:36:05.980 --> 00:36:07.464
You killed him!

467
00:36:07.532 --> 00:36:08.798
He died.

468
00:36:11.519 --> 00:36:13.036
Like your sister died?

469
00:36:13.104 --> 00:36:15.705
My sister was missing.

470
00:36:15.773 --> 00:36:17.958
I came here looking for her.

471
00:36:18.994 --> 00:36:20.076
You found her.

472
00:36:20.144 --> 00:36:22.245
I found her in pieces.

473
00:36:22.313 --> 00:36:24.163
being used as bait to catch me.

474
00:36:25.650 --> 00:36:28.852
I think you killed them both.

475
00:36:28.920 --> 00:36:32.071
I'm gonna tell everyone.
starting with the sheriff.

476
00:37:10.712 --> 00:37:11.811
Huh.

477
00:37:13.348 --> 00:37:15.815
That was cute.

478
00:38:59.253 --> 00:39:00.303
I didn't kill him.

479
00:39:01.289 --> 00:39:03.122
Neither of us did.

480
00:39:03.190 --> 00:39:04.950
It's not your fault.
and it's not mine.

481
00:39:05.861 --> 00:39:07.293
This?

482
00:39:07.361 --> 00:39:08.995
This is all your fault!

483
00:39:09.064 --> 00:39:10.463
You ruined my life!

484
00:39:11.599 --> 00:39:13.049
No. I didn't.

485
00:39:13.985 --> 00:39:15.179
You're the one who bit me!

486
00:39:15.203 --> 00:39:16.519
No. I'm not.

487
00:39:17.989 --> 00:39:19.439
What!

488
00:39:19.508 --> 00:39:21.574
I'm not the one that bit you.

489
00:39:47.818 --> 00:39:49.285
There's another.

490
00:39:49.354 --> 00:39:50.819
It's called an Alpha.

491
00:39:50.888 --> 00:39:53.456
It's the most
dangerous of our kind.

492
00:39:53.525 --> 00:39:55.041
You and I. we're Betas.

493
00:39:56.128 --> 00:39:59.562
This thing is more powerful.

494
00:39:59.631 --> 00:40:02.681
more animal than either of us.

495
00:40:02.750 --> 00:40:04.667
My sister came
here looking for him.

496
00:40:04.736 --> 00:40:08.204
Now I'm trying to find him. But I
don't think I can do it without you.

497
00:40:11.242 --> 00:40:12.741
Why me?

498
00:40:12.810 --> 00:40:16.528
Because he's the one that
bit you. You're part of his pack.

499
00:40:20.168 --> 00:40:21.651
It's you. Scott.

500
00:40:24.656 --> 00:40:25.749
You're the one he wants.
